cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on integrating UAVs into the cellular network to enhance communication performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with trajectory optimization of UAVs, which is a common problem in robotics. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the quality-of-connectivity constraint of the GBS-UAV link, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes methods to optimize the UAV trajectory, which is a control problem. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed methods for trajectory optimization involve graph theory and convex optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence.
